HEADWORD: Euphonical
<hw>Eu*phon"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or exhibiting,
euphony; agreeable in sound; pleasing to the ear; euphonious; <as>as, a
<ex>euphonic</ex> expression; <ex>euphonical</ex>
orthography.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

